.TH "dma_fence_begin_signalling" 9 "dma_fence_begin_signalling" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dma_fence_begin_signalling \- begin a critical DMA fence signalling section
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" dma_fence_begin_signalling
.BI "(void "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "void" 12
no arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Drivers should use this to annotate the beginning of any code section
required to eventually complete \fIdma_fence\fP by calling \fBdma_fence_signal\fP.

The end of these critical sections are annotated with
\fBdma_fence_end_signalling\fP.

Opaque cookie needed by the implementation, which needs to be passed to
\fBdma_fence_end_signalling\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
